groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: View of I-95
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description: What happens when they build a new bridge next to the old bridge? Well they make a new road of course. Good thing for us because these sites make great Geo hide locations. Here is one of them that even the kids can do but you still have to be careful because of the main road only a couple of yards away. This one is magnetic but does not look magnetic. If you drive to the end of the cal de sac you have a good view of I-95.
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:encoded_hints: It is not on the guardrail and it is not electric, but it looks like it could be ;-)

groundspeak:log.groundspeak:text: Quick find with dawnie22 on our way down I-95. TFTC
